article.headline: Belmont 87, Gardner-Webb 55
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Andy Wicke hit 10-of-12 3-pointers and scored 31 points as hot-shooting Belmont beat Gardner-Webb 87-55 Thursday night. The Bruins (17-9, 11-4 Atlantic Sun Conference) shot 52.6 percent from the floor and led nearly all the game. Ten of Belmont's 12 players scored as Gardner-Webb (9-18, 7-9) hit just 32.8 percent from the field. The Bruins had 39 bench points to 18 for Gardner-Webb. Reserve Justin Hare added 16 points for Belmont, and had nine rebounds to tie for the team lead with Matthew Dotson. The Runnin' Bulldogs were led by Grayson Flittner with 12 points and Chris Gash with 10. Belmont controlled the boards 47-24. It was 47-27 at halftime.
